.TH "drm_plane_init" 9 "drm_plane_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_plane_init \- Initialize a legacy plane
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_plane_init
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_plane *plane "  ","
.BI "uint32_t possible_crtcs "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_plane_funcs *funcs "  ","
.BI "const uint32_t *formats "  ","
.BI "unsigned int format_count "  ","
.BI "bool is_primary "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "plane" 12
plane object to init
.IP "possible_crtcs" 12
bitmask of possible CRTCs
.IP "funcs" 12
callbacks for the new plane
.IP "formats" 12
array of supported formats (DRM_FORMAT\_\*)
.IP "format_count" 12
number of elements in \fIformats\fP
.IP "is_primary" 12
plane type (primary vs overlay)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Legacy API to initialize a DRM plane.

New drivers should call \fBdrm_universal_plane_init\fP instead.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, error code on failure.
